Sentencas: The GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+delta (GBCCF) layered perovskite oxide was evaluated as novel cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Evaluation of GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its electrical conductivity was 9-13 S cm(-1) at 650-800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of GBCCF was 14.4 x 10(-6) K-1 which was close to that of the typical electrolyte material.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathode polarization resistance of GBCCF was 0.650 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C and it decreases to 0.118 Omega cm(2) when Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) was added to form a GBCCF GDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Preliminary results indicated that layered perovskite GBCCF was a promising alternative cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdBaCuCo0.5Fe0.5O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
